[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Clarifying object serialization**\n\nI’m thinking about how `writeObject` works in serialization. If it’s used, the class data comes from \"values written by `writeObject`,\" and it's not automatic. The class description still has a list of fields, but when `writeSerialData` is called, it only invokes `writeObject`, not providing defaults. On the other hand, `ObjectInputStream` won’t read the field values automatically unless `readObject` is invoked. So, the class description has fields, but default data isn't present.\n\n**Evaluating class structure**\n\nI’m considering the fields and how there's a custom writeObject without a default. It looks like the class description includes the fields, and JCEDH's readObject should read the custom data, so it should work. However, I’m wondering if there’s a class hierarchy mismatch since the helper extends Object and the target also extends Object. I think this is a crucial point to clarify!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f3f90e3fcdb0f0d0169fbee720da081a2bdf05b840a7201fe\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp--6F6neguCKlQFthqjQfSDmgTQG_y4zZ9VZsjDf8hoix7RuLvVLv_4NouzyjRfkJZRgLnNCRW7SZAQsSx2k4oRxUesvfrIzj5zXCLeWEfYC32YXcSm2GXg2iVYjqo-sWwkcrflEhZ0p1ACbatBR031imkoGhcWTAHSaRArYCk_ArPVMwhqODOZzxfhKwcqNAosqYksWrv9uSXuwJJoL80Q_nvA2-yas5Ql2fVsWoSUuGWiyaUi7QSR_IQBCM3-UViXkPWdlOekGSfE3KHNfwGDG-wZJG0ZyEDLhsFxAxD5uyou7TD_jbuZJV-jpD1flAyXcOskJtFe7NChNMlmicMcy2LISqn-oXafGOIjUwf-o94LVxL2fghiJhCGiEVC4iKMfSNQVRw8nDcAUFFmWrxNYYlNAB9AG7eALrqT0oGqn8P4qZUYYr342QC8AdcA4Pv45Bf9ARJ7gguqeNY46ychgInssbXWKdLw7bMVIGcjkFnmjumPZdAY4Zxwa7kMhoHu1i3ZPh83B-VrIgKBU4rrnZ-hbYicMYwvP46WIr_Jc4tsKWpgYVlmUklLLqGrEWzidyS2HbzMDg5RqByDEqWKzaV5ItsLzYI79x0-9JvJuLsivNfRKvQssoC1KcDM_q1zmhYS2nd_OSjQ4bUYnGlxG1igegwvBpudm6fgRd8uIkXv0wukr2Zc6n2W4G7Z8QAcNapKEqXuG5wC0evAGibE1knubCvwY6xYOcq7pPLJ_r2UgOA5_z30zBxl2fKdjK5b6Rrn377LUmPi3kzaz-buxBwtqb5